      "inheritance_hierarchy": "SecondSwap_Marketplace inherits OZ Initializable. SecondSwap_VestingManager inherits IVestingManager and OZ Initializable. SecondSwap_VestingDeployer inherits OZ Initializable. SecondSwap_StepVesting implements SecondSwap_Vesting interface. SecondSwap_MarketplaceSetting implements IMarketplaceSetting interface. SecondSwap_Whitelist implements IWhitelist interface. No proxy base contracts are present in-code; upgradeability intended via external proxy deployments for Initializable contracts.",
      "external_dependencies": [
        "OpenZeppelin: Initializable (upgradeable utils)",
        "OpenZeppelin: SafeERC20 (token transfer wrappers)",
        "OpenZeppelin: IERC20",
        "OpenZeppelin: Math (min)",
        "Interfaces: SecondSwap_IMarketplaceSetting, SecondSwap_IVestingManager, SecondSwap_Vesting, SecondSwap_IWhitelist, IERC20 (local interface file)",
        "Hardhat console.sol (debug import; should not be present in production deployments)"
      ],
      "upgrade_patterns": "UUPS/Transparent proxies are not explicitly implemented in the provided code, but multiple contracts are Initializable and lack constructors (Marketplace, VestingManager, VestingDeployer), implying deployment behind a proxy. No upgrade authorization (UUPS _authorizeUpgrade) is present, so if used, pattern is likely Transparent proxy with external ProxyAdmin, or another custom proxy. StepVesting, MarketplaceSetting, Whitelist, WhitelistDeployer are non-upgradeable (constructors / immutables).",
      "access_control_structure": "Predominantly single-admin model via MarketplaceSetting.s2Admin and VestingManager.s2Admin plus role-like addresses (marketplace, vestingDeployer, tokenIssuer). Marketplace reads admin from MarketplaceSetting for addCoin/setMarketplaceSettingAddress and unlist authorization. VestingManager gates core flows with onlyMarketplace and onlyAdmin; setSellable is dual-authorized (s2Admin or vestingDeployer); setMaxSellPercent requires tokenIssuer of the specific StepVesting. VestingDeployer has onlyAdmin for configuration and uses _tokenOwner mapping for issuer authorization. Whitelist uses immutable lotOwner for max changes; self-service allowlist via whitelistAddress().",
      "inventories_note": "No Diamond storage pattern detected; no facet/proxy contracts included."
    },
